Excessive requirements for public procurement applications will be excluded by law
The legislation may establish comprehensive requirements for applications for participation in procurement.
In the autumn session, at the plenary session of the State Duma, it is planned to consider in the second reading a draft law establishing the requirements for the content and composition of the application for participation in the procurement, participants of which can only be small and medium-sized businesses.
Amendments are made by the government to the law "On the procurement of goods, works, services by certain types of legal entities."
The bill was developed in pursuance of the roadmap for the implementation of the Strategy for the Development of Small and Medium-Sized Businesses in the Russian Federation until 2030, approved by the government.
It provides for the preparation of a draft law on an exhaustive list of documents that customers have the right to require as part of an application from procurement participants - small and medium-sized businesses.
And also - about the list of requirements for these documents.
Today, the law "On the procurement of goods, works, services by certain types of legal entities" regulates the procurement activities of certain types of legal entities.
Requirements for the content, form, design and composition of the application for participation in the procurement are established by the customers independently in the procurement documentation.
"As a result, the customers establish excessive requirements for the content, execution of the application, the mandatory presence in its composition of references, certificates, extracts, the time of receipt of which in the authorized bodies is comparable to the deadline for submitting applications, which leads to the impossibility of participating in such a procurement and a reduction in the number of procurement participants" , - says the explanation to the bill.
The new bill provides for the establishment of an exhaustive list of documents that customers have the right to require as part of an application from procurement participants who are small and medium-sized businesses.
"The adoption of the document will allow to exclude the arbitrary establishment by customers of requirements for the composition and content of applications of participants who are small and medium-sized businesses," the explanatory note says.
As an artist, connection is very important to me.
In my works, I try to show that people are inseparable from nature and that everything is interconnected.
I first visited Antarctica almost 10 years ago, and there I saw icebergs.
I was in awe.
My heart was beating faster, my head was spinning, trying to understand what opened in front of me.
The icebergs around were floating out of the water nearly 200 feet. And I could not help but be surprised that this is one snowflake on top of another, year after year.
Icebergs are born when they break off glacier ice or break off ice shelves.
Each iceberg has its own personality.
Everyone interacts with the environment in their own way and gains their own experience.
Some refuse to give up and hold on to the bitter end, while others can no longer fight and die in a fit of intense passion.
Looking at an iceberg, it is easy to think that it is isolated, that it is closed and alone, just as we humans often see ourselves.
But in life, everything is completely different.
When an iceberg melts, I breathe in its ancient atmosphere.
When an iceberg melts, it releases fresh, mineral-rich water that feeds many life forms.
I approach photographing these icebergs as portraying my ancestors, knowing that in these individual moments they exist in this very image, and that it will never happen again.
They don't die when they melt; it is not the end, but the continuation of their path in the cycle of life.
Sometimes the ice in the icebergs that I photograph is very young - only a couple of thousand years old.
And some icebergs are over 100,000 years old.
The last photos I want to show you are of an iceberg I photographed in Kirtartivatziak, Greenland.
It is a very rare case when it is possible to see how an iceberg rotates.
So here it is.
A small boat is visible on the left.
Approximately 4.5 meters long.
Please pay attention to the shape of the iceberg and where it touches the water.
Here you can see how it begins to rotate, and the boat swam across to the other side, and there is a man.
This is a medium-sized Greenlandic iceberg.
It protrudes from the water about 120 feet or 40 meters.
And here is this real-time recording.
(Music) And just like that, the iceberg shows us a different side of his personality.
Thank you.
